    <string name="edu_5_layers_intro">Our system evaluates stocks through 5 distinct \"Layers\" of analysis. A stock must pass the earlier layers before the later layers matter. We use these tags to quickly identify the current state of a stock.</string>
    <string name="edu_bollinger_content">A \'Volatility Tube\' that wraps around price. \n\n• Lower Band (Value): Prices here are statistically cheap for their current movement.\n• Upper Band (Resistance): Prices here are stretched too far. High risk of a reversal.</string>
    <string name="edu_bollinger_title">Bollinger Bands (Volatility Map)</string>
    <string name="edu_golden_rule_content">SELL signals ALWAYS override BUY signals. If a stock has great momentum but hits RSI 65 or the Upper Bollinger Band, the app will warn you to wait. Never buy at the peak!</string>
    <string name="edu_golden_rule_title">The Golden Rule</string>
    <string formatted="false" name="edu_layer_1_content">The foundation. Does the company make money? We look for ROE > 15%, Net Profit Margin > 10%, consistent 3Y profit growth, and low debt (D/E &lt; 1.5).</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_1_title">Layer 1: QUAL (Quality/Fundamentals)</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_2_content">Is the price fair? Even a great company is a bad investment if you pay too much. We compare Current P/E to Historical P/E and check Price-to-Book ratios.</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_2_title">Layer 2: VAL (Valuation)</string>
    <string formatted="false" name="edu_layer_3_content">For income investors. We accumulate and compound high-yield stocks (> 5%) indefinitely. Keep holding and reinvesting dividends unless fundamentals break (ROE &lt; 15% or high debt) or the dividend yield drops below 3%.</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_3_title">Layer 3: DIV (Dividend)</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_4_content">Are buyers stepping in? We use MACD crossovers and moving averages to confirm that the trend has actually shifted to the upside. Never catch a falling knife.</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_4_title">Layer 4: MOM (Momentum)</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_5_content">The trigger. We use RSI (Relative Strength Index) to find when prices are \'oversold\' (RSI &lt; 35) at major support levels, providing a low-risk entry point.</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_5_title">Layer 5: SUP (Support/Technicals)</string>
    <string name="edu_macd_content">Think of this as the car\'s gears. Even if a stock is cheap (RSI 35), we look for the MACD Histogram to turn positive. This confirms that the momentum has shifted to the upside.</string>
    <string name="edu_macd_title">MACD (The Momentum Switch)</string>
    <string formatted="false" name="edu_risk_mgmt_content">The most important rule in trading is preserving your capital. \n\n• Why: Small losses are easy to recover. A -50% loss requires a +100% gain just to break even.\n• When: If a stock drops -5% from your cost, the app will trigger a SELL signal. This is your cue to exit and protect your remaining cash.</string>
    <string name="edu_risk_mgmt_title">The Art of the \'Cut Loss\'</string>
    <string name="edu_rsi_content">The Relative Strength Index (14 days). \n\n• Target 35 (Value): The stock is oversold. Prices are \'compressed\' and ready to bounce.\n• Target 65 (Caution): The stock is overbought. Risk of a pullback is high.</string>
    <string name="edu_rsi_title">RSI (The Speedometer)</string>
    <string name="edu_sma_content">Moving Averages track the \'Average\' price over time.\n\n• SMA 200: The long-term \'Line in the Sand\'. Above this is a healthy Bull Market.\n• SMA 50: Mid-term health. Price above this suggests the trend is your friend.</string>
    <string name="edu_sma_title">SMA 50 &amp; 200 (Trend Guards)</string>
    <string formatted="false" name="edu_step1_content">Don\'t gamble on random stocks. Use the \'+\' button to import curated collections like \'Dividend Stars\' or \'Bluechips\'. Look for the \'Solid Financials\' badge—these companies have high ROE (>15%), low debt (D/E &lt; 1.5), and strong profit margins.</string>
    <string name="edu_step1_title">1. Discovery (Quality First)</string>
    <string name="edu_step2_content">Move stocks into your Watchlist. The app monitors them 24/7:\n\n• AMBER (Potential): RSI &lt; 42. The stock is getting cheap or testing support.\n• GREEN (Buy): RSI &lt; 35 or confirmed momentum. Confirmed value + confirmed momentum.</string>
    <string name="edu_step2_title">2. Monitoring (The Traffic Lights)</string>
    <string formatted="false" name="edu_step3_content">When you see a Buy signal, use the \'Risk/Reward Calculator\'. Set a target (+10-20%) and a stop loss (-5%). Swing trades are held for a short period of 2–4 weeks. If the math doesn\'t show at least 2x reward for your risk, wait for a better price.</string>
    <string name="edu_step3_title">3. Execution (The Plan)</string>
    <string name="edu_workflow_subtitle">Disciplined steps for consistent profit.</string>
    <string name="edu_workflow_title">Master the Workflow</string>
    <string formatted="false" name="edu_yoc_content">We evaluate the \'DNA\' of every company before suggesting it. A stock earns the \'⭐ Quality\' tag if it meets these strict checks:\n\n• ROE > 15%: Superior management efficiency.\n• Net Profit Margin > 10%: Healthy business profitability.\n• Profit Growth (3Y) > 10%: Consistent bottom-line growth.\n• D/E Ratio &lt; 1.5: Safe levels of financial debt.</string>
    <string name="edu_yoc_title">Fundamental Guardrails</string>
